        <tr><td>Real-time updates</td><td>Broadcast order status changes to customers via Laravel Reverb / Pusher WebSockets</td><td>High</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Order confirmation</td><td>Email receipt to customer on order placement via OtpMail pattern</td><td>High</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Product images</td><td>Photo gallery using S3 driver + spatie/laravel-medialibrary for automatic resizing</td><td>Medium</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Search</td><td>Laravel Scout + Meilisearch for typo-tolerant, relevance-ranked results</td><td>Medium</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Delivery tracking</td><td>Shiprocket / Delhivery API integration for live courier status inside the orders page</td><td>Medium</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Reviews</td><td>Star ratings and customer reviews per product with spam detection</td><td>Low</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Loyalty programme</td><td>Points earned per purchase, redeemable at checkout</td><td>Low</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Mobile app</td><td>Versioned JSON API with Sanctum tokens for a React Native or Flutter client</td><td>Low</td></tr>
        <tr><td>CI/CD</td><td>GitHub Actions: Pint lint → PHPUnit → Docker build → Vercel deploy</td><td>Medium</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="s14">
    <p class="sec-num">Section 14</p>
    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>FruGo demonstrates a modern Laravel e-commerce application with a well-reasoned authentication strategy, efficient session-based cart implementation, and a deployment architecture that spans both traditional Docker containers and modern serverless infrastructure.</p>
    <p>The passwordless OTP authentication removes the single largest barrier to customer conversion — account creation — whilst maintaining strong security guarantees through hashed token storage, immediate token deletion, and enforced expiry. The session cart eliminates unnecessary database writes during the browsing phase and provides a zero-query cart count visible on every page.</p>
    <p>The Vercel adaptation demonstrates that Laravel can be deployed to serverless PHP runtimes with careful attention to the filesystem model — a technique applicable to any Laravel application targeting cloud functions or edge compute environments.</p>
    <div class="note"><strong>Repository</strong>Source code, deployment scripts, and configuration: <strong>github.com/vasant24konar/FruGo</strong></div>
  </section>

